4 likes, 0 comments - robertmenziesinstitute on May 2, 2024: "Home is where the heart is üè°üìö‚ù§Ô∏è

Nestled within a leafy canopy on Howard Street, Kew sits the former home of Robert Menzies. Earlier this week, we took a tour of the historic site. Brimming with ornate stained glass and rich mahogany, the interior remains much the same as when Menzies resided in the property. 

With gratitude and humility, we treasured the chance to step into Sir Robert's world. Living in this home for more than 20yrs, he filled it with several unique artefacts, including a perfectly preserved driveshaft from a Japanese miniature submarine sunk in Sydney Harbour during World War II.

What an honour to hold a piece of history in our hand!".
